WEBVTT

00:00:09.417 --> 00:00:10.958
-[BAAL] Kiriwo...
-[KIRIWO chuckles]

00:00:11.000 --> 00:00:13.625
[BAAL] ...you're not wrong
about any of this.

00:00:13.667 --> 00:00:15.208
Now do your duty!

00:00:19.083 --> 00:00:20.917
[shatters]

00:00:20.958 --> 00:00:24.167
-Hmm?
-[explosion booms]

00:00:24.208 --> 00:00:26.708
[ALL screaming]

00:00:28.958 --> 00:00:30.667
[screams]

00:00:30.708 --> 00:00:32.042
What in the world?!

00:00:32.083 --> 00:00:33.208
[screams]

00:00:45.125 --> 00:00:47.875
Calm down! Make sure the
students and staff are alright!

00:00:47.917 --> 00:00:50.458
All faculty should check
their stations! Hurry!

00:00:51.958 --> 00:00:52.958
[gasps]

00:00:55.042 --> 00:00:57.667
There's a wall,
and it's invisible?!

00:00:57.708 --> 00:01:00.042
Yeah, you're right!
Something's here!

00:01:00.083 --> 00:01:01.458
[BOY 1]
What's going on?

00:01:01.500 --> 00:01:03.083
[BOY 2] There are invisible
walls everywhere!

00:01:03.125 --> 00:01:04.708
[BOY 3]
Are we trapped inside?

00:01:04.750 --> 00:01:06.500
[GIRL]
Wait, seriously?

00:01:12.875 --> 00:01:14.500
[KIRIWO]
Hmm. Now, then...

00:01:15.625 --> 00:01:17.833
...let's get
the real party started!

00:01:21.542 --> 00:01:23.583
[NARRATOR]
Iruma Suzuki, age fourteen.

00:01:23.625 --> 00:01:25.042
One day, he found himself

00:01:25.083 --> 00:01:26.958
the grandson
of a demon named Sullivan.

00:01:28.125 --> 00:01:30.375
Sullivan loves
and spoils Iruma

00:01:30.417 --> 00:01:32.917
and is even sending him
to the most prestigious school

00:01:32.958 --> 00:01:33.917
in the land.

00:01:33.958 --> 00:01:36.292
But there is just one problem.

00:01:36.333 --> 00:01:38.042
The school Iruma is attending

00:01:38.083 --> 00:01:39.833
just so happens to be

00:01:39.875 --> 00:01:42.583
the demon school
known as Babyls.

00:01:42.625 --> 00:01:45.042
[IRUMA] I can't ever
let them find out I'm human,

00:01:45.083 --> 00:01:47.042
or I'm gonna get eaten
for sure!

00:03:20.750 --> 00:03:23.708
[IRUMA/ASMODEUS/CLARA]
"Run, Iruma, to Kiriwo!"

00:03:29.583 --> 00:03:31.625
There are walls everywhere.

00:03:31.667 --> 00:03:34.333
You're right, and the scale
of them is unreal.

00:03:34.375 --> 00:03:36.042
-Hmmm!
-Hmm?

00:03:36.083 --> 00:03:37.750
Did you find
a wall there, too?

00:03:37.792 --> 00:03:38.917
Not a one!

00:03:38.958 --> 00:03:41.042
Why do you complicate
everything?!

00:03:41.083 --> 00:03:42.083
-[IRUMA] Hey.
-[BOTH] Huh?

00:03:43.083 --> 00:03:44.917
This barrier here...

00:03:44.958 --> 00:03:47.500
Wait, is this... a wall?

00:03:47.542 --> 00:03:48.708
Hiyah!

00:03:50.125 --> 00:03:52.208
Hey, there's something
right there!

00:03:52.250 --> 00:03:54.125
My stars,
it's an invisible wall.

00:03:54.167 --> 00:03:56.292
-Oh yay!
-Isn't it great?

00:03:56.333 --> 00:03:59.083
It's my bloodline ability,
Barrier.

00:04:00.750 --> 00:04:02.417
Isn't it one of Kiriwo's?

00:04:04.125 --> 00:04:06.500
[GAAKO] All that shaking before
was so scary.

00:04:06.542 --> 00:04:07.542
[EIKO]
Right?

00:04:07.583 --> 00:04:09.875
Gosh, I wonder
if Iruma's okay.

00:04:09.917 --> 00:04:11.083
-[thud]
-[grunts]

00:04:11.125 --> 00:04:12.250
-Huh?
-What's the matter with y--

00:04:12.292 --> 00:04:13.292
-[thud]
-[grunts]

00:04:16.667 --> 00:04:17.958
[EIKO]
A wall...

00:04:19.667 --> 00:04:21.875
[humming]

00:04:21.917 --> 00:04:22.875
-[thud]
-[yelps]

00:04:24.292 --> 00:04:26.875
Do-san-ko was here!

00:04:26.917 --> 00:04:28.042
[BOY 1]
What's going on?

00:04:29.000 --> 00:04:30.500
[GIRL 1]
I can't get through here!

00:04:30.542 --> 00:04:31.792
[BOY 2]
Or here!

00:04:31.833 --> 00:04:32.792
[GIRL 2]
Acchan!

00:04:32.833 --> 00:04:33.917
[BOY 3]
Bakemi!

00:04:33.958 --> 00:04:35.708
[BOY 4]
Take that!

00:04:35.750 --> 00:04:37.125
Aw, it's no use.

00:04:37.167 --> 00:04:38.583
So basically,
we're trapped

00:04:38.625 --> 00:04:40.875
in here with no way in
or out?

00:04:40.917 --> 00:04:42.708
[KONATSU]
I wonder what's going on.

00:04:42.750 --> 00:04:45.417
Apparently, there are walls
everywhere, inside and out.

00:04:45.458 --> 00:04:46.708
Well, this sucks.

00:04:46.750 --> 00:04:48.625
I wanted to go home
before the Party Day

00:04:48.667 --> 00:04:50.667
to change
into something super cute.

00:04:50.708 --> 00:04:52.625
[HARUNO]
All I want is a shower.

00:04:52.667 --> 00:04:54.583
[BOY 1] Someone get
the teachers over here.

00:04:54.625 --> 00:04:57.500
[BOY 2] I'm pretty sure
this is only gonna get worse.

00:04:57.542 --> 00:05:00.500
[COME-COME] You've got this,
just keep on keeping on!

00:05:00.542 --> 00:05:01.917
Protect the wares.

00:05:01.958 --> 00:05:04.167
[straining]

00:05:04.208 --> 00:05:06.708
[ALL panting]

00:05:06.750 --> 00:05:09.417
Sorry for intruding, President,
but the panic is spreading!

00:05:09.458 --> 00:05:12.708
It seems there are invisible
barriers all around the school--

00:05:12.750 --> 00:05:15.208
-[ALL grunt]
-There's one in here, too?

00:05:15.250 --> 00:05:17.875
-Hey, I found a gap over here.
-Hmm?

00:05:17.917 --> 00:05:19.667
Su-ki-ma?

00:05:20.625 --> 00:05:22.292
What shall we do?

00:05:22.333 --> 00:05:23.333
[sighs]

00:05:23.375 --> 00:05:24.583
A barrier, huh?

00:05:25.750 --> 00:05:27.375
Barrier.

00:05:27.417 --> 00:05:29.917
Come to think of it,
there was that classic scene

00:05:29.958 --> 00:05:33.042
where those two had a pane
of glass between them.

00:05:33.083 --> 00:05:35.917
Kakeru had run away
from the evil organization

00:05:35.958 --> 00:05:37.125
and had to hide.

00:05:37.167 --> 00:05:39.083
-[RIN] Kakeru!
-[KAKERU] Rin!

00:05:39.125 --> 00:05:41.667
-[giggles]
-[QUICHE] President?

00:05:41.708 --> 00:05:42.833
Aah!

00:05:42.875 --> 00:05:44.417
Don't you panic!

00:05:44.458 --> 00:05:45.958
For we,
the student council,

00:05:46.000 --> 00:05:48.083
must set an example
for other students.

00:05:48.125 --> 00:05:49.917
If we are panicking,
then everyone else

00:05:49.958 --> 00:05:51.417
will just panic more.

00:05:51.458 --> 00:05:53.208
Calmly assess our situation

00:05:53.250 --> 00:05:55.292
and make sure
the students are safe.

00:05:55.333 --> 00:05:56.792
[SUNNY/JOHNNY/QUICHE/SMOKE]
Will do, boss!

00:06:00.583 --> 00:06:03.250
[AMERI] What in the netherworld
is going on around here?

00:06:05.917 --> 00:06:07.125
-[thud]
-Ow!

00:06:07.167 --> 00:06:08.333
[chomps]

00:06:10.833 --> 00:06:12.250
Upsy-daisy!

00:06:12.292 --> 00:06:13.500
Huh?

00:06:13.542 --> 00:06:16.250
I wonder
what this barrier could be.

00:06:16.292 --> 00:06:18.583
This thing won't budge an inch!
It's rock solid!

00:06:19.542 --> 00:06:22.542
Oh, I get it! I bet
this is like a mystery game.

00:06:22.583 --> 00:06:23.875
A surprise, yeah?

00:06:23.917 --> 00:06:25.708
What are you babbling about?

00:06:25.750 --> 00:06:27.625
I'm just wondering
who you think left

00:06:27.667 --> 00:06:30.750
this surprise for us to uncover,
Acting Chair-Demon Kalego?

00:06:30.792 --> 00:06:33.042
Stop calling me that. Move.

00:06:34.000 --> 00:06:35.417
Cerberobuth, out!

00:06:35.458 --> 00:06:38.000
[roaring]

00:06:44.917 --> 00:06:47.292
[gasps, laughs]

00:06:47.333 --> 00:06:49.833
So cool!

00:06:54.083 --> 00:06:57.125
The heck?!
It sealed itself up again?

00:06:57.167 --> 00:06:59.042
[KALEGO]
What the hell is this?

00:06:59.083 --> 00:07:00.792
How much magic is necessary

00:07:00.833 --> 00:07:03.542
to make a barrier
this resilient?

00:07:03.583 --> 00:07:06.000
Maybe a Tet? No.

00:07:06.042 --> 00:07:09.083
Something like this could
withstand everything except

00:07:09.125 --> 00:07:12.250
the magic
of a Yodh-ranked demon.

00:07:12.292 --> 00:07:13.708
Hmm.

00:07:13.750 --> 00:07:16.167
On that note, is this
also connected to the fact

00:07:16.208 --> 00:07:19.250
that that fool of a chair-demon
is being detained?

00:07:19.292 --> 00:07:20.625
Perhaps someone
had him confined

00:07:20.667 --> 00:07:22.375
so he wouldn't be able
to destroy it.

00:07:23.833 --> 00:07:25.208
Newbie. Follow me.

00:07:25.250 --> 00:07:26.708
Huh? Where are we going?

00:07:26.750 --> 00:07:28.542
To the management warehouse.

00:07:28.583 --> 00:07:30.583
But you saw it,
there's a barrier here.

00:07:30.625 --> 00:07:32.208
So how are we going to...

00:07:32.250 --> 00:07:34.583
[roars]

00:07:34.625 --> 00:07:35.792
[KALEGO]
Cerberobuth.

00:07:37.125 --> 00:07:39.125
[roaring]

00:07:40.208 --> 00:07:41.667
[KALEGO]
Cerberobuth.

00:07:47.042 --> 00:07:49.167
Wow, that's so awesome!

00:07:52.792 --> 00:07:54.208
You are just amazing,

00:07:54.250 --> 00:07:55.667
-Acting Chair-Demon!
-Silence.

00:07:55.708 --> 00:07:57.042
Oop!

00:07:57.083 --> 00:07:58.833
You wanted a surprise?

00:08:00.167 --> 00:08:03.042
Well, newbie,
I will employ your idea.

00:08:03.083 --> 00:08:04.125
Huh?

00:08:06.500 --> 00:08:08.792
-Hello, Dali,
-Kalego, sir!

00:08:08.833 --> 00:08:11.625
We seem to be having
a genuine emergency.

00:08:11.667 --> 00:08:14.292
The students are panicking
and-- Huh?

00:08:14.333 --> 00:08:16.250
Ah, that's wonderful!

00:08:18.417 --> 00:08:20.167
[shrieking]

00:08:23.667 --> 00:08:25.125
[ALL]
Hmm?

00:08:25.167 --> 00:08:26.708
[DALI] [on PA]
Hello, students.

00:08:26.750 --> 00:08:28.583
Can you all hear me clearly?

00:08:28.625 --> 00:08:29.875
[BOY]
Professor Dali!

00:08:29.917 --> 00:08:31.792
[DALI]
Did that surprise you?

00:08:31.833 --> 00:08:33.750
Well, you can all relax!

00:08:33.792 --> 00:08:35.333
This was a surprise event

00:08:35.375 --> 00:08:38.500
created by the New Magic Battler
and the Game Battler.

00:08:38.542 --> 00:08:40.583
-What? It's a surprise?
-[STUDENTS murmuring]

00:08:40.625 --> 00:08:42.542
So, is this, like, a game?

00:08:42.583 --> 00:08:43.792
[BOY]
I see.

00:08:43.833 --> 00:08:46.708
[DALI] The whole school
is now a maze!

00:08:50.333 --> 00:08:51.625
Hey, President,

00:08:51.667 --> 00:08:53.542
we didn't actually cast
this spell, did we?

00:08:53.583 --> 00:08:54.833
No way.

00:08:54.875 --> 00:08:56.792
This game is news
to our group as well.

00:08:56.833 --> 00:08:59.292
[DALI] Avoid those nasty
invisible walls

00:08:59.333 --> 00:09:02.125
and head toward the goal:
the central plaza!

00:09:02.167 --> 00:09:05.000
Huh, let's try going
this way.

00:09:05.042 --> 00:09:06.167
-[thud]
-Ohh!

00:09:07.250 --> 00:09:09.958
As the saying goes,
always make your mark.

00:09:10.000 --> 00:09:12.500
[DALI] We even have prizes
for the winners!

00:09:12.542 --> 00:09:14.958
-So, get fired up!
-[ALL] Ahh!

00:09:15.000 --> 00:09:17.250
[straining]

00:09:20.250 --> 00:09:21.875
[COME-COME]
Yay, surprises!

00:09:21.917 --> 00:09:24.000
-Gonna get out of this maze!
-Hey!

00:09:24.042 --> 00:09:26.083
You guys hurry up, now!

00:09:27.292 --> 00:09:28.417
And scene.

00:09:28.458 --> 00:09:30.250
That's the whole act.

00:09:30.292 --> 00:09:33.125
Thanks a lot!
You Broadcast Battlers rule!

00:09:33.167 --> 00:09:34.500
Sure.

00:09:34.542 --> 00:09:37.208
Are you sure this is alright,
Professor Dali?

00:09:37.250 --> 00:09:39.000
This wasn't listed
in the program.

00:09:39.042 --> 00:09:40.542
[chuckles]

00:09:40.583 --> 00:09:43.208
It was a surprise,
like I said.

00:09:43.250 --> 00:09:46.917
-Right, Professor Kalego?
-[KALEGO] Yes.

00:09:46.958 --> 00:09:48.333
Whatever happens,
we're not going

00:09:48.375 --> 00:09:50.042
to let this ruin the party.

00:09:50.083 --> 00:09:51.958
I'll make sure to get
the New Magic Battler

00:09:52.000 --> 00:09:55.083
and the Game Battler
on the same page a bit later.

00:09:55.125 --> 00:09:56.875
Nothing to worry about!

00:09:56.917 --> 00:09:59.625
[KALEGO] Hmm. That's an
acceptable stopgap measure.

00:09:59.667 --> 00:10:02.708
We don't want mass confusion
among the students.

00:10:02.750 --> 00:10:06.083
-However...
-[pulsing]

00:10:06.125 --> 00:10:08.000
All teachers
in the central plaza,

00:10:08.042 --> 00:10:10.542
organize the students
who show up and take roll.

00:10:10.583 --> 00:10:12.167
-Roger that, sir.
-Yis, sir.

00:10:12.208 --> 00:10:14.292
[KALEGO] The rest of you,
try to figure this out.

00:10:14.333 --> 00:10:16.167
Sir!

00:10:16.208 --> 00:10:17.708
And go!

00:10:17.750 --> 00:10:19.667
[croaking]

00:10:19.708 --> 00:10:21.708
Newbie, aid me.

00:10:21.750 --> 00:10:23.958
Yes, sir.
How can I be of service?

00:10:26.292 --> 00:10:27.792
[laughs]
Wow!

00:10:27.833 --> 00:10:29.542
Documents for days!

00:10:30.917 --> 00:10:33.375
[KALEGO] All there is to know
about Babyls lives in here.

00:10:34.375 --> 00:10:37.125
Anyone who can create a barrier
is a real suspect.

00:10:37.167 --> 00:10:39.208
We're going to narrow
them down one by one.

00:10:39.250 --> 00:10:41.958
From all these? Really?

00:10:42.000 --> 00:10:43.208
Huh?

00:10:43.250 --> 00:10:46.042
Come hither,
the goal's this way! Yis.

00:10:46.083 --> 00:10:48.000
Yay! I think I'm
the first here!

00:10:48.042 --> 00:10:49.250
[HARUNO/AZUKI/KONATSU]
Dosa!

00:10:49.292 --> 00:10:51.500
Uh-huh.
Finally, we meet again.

00:10:51.542 --> 00:10:53.458
I wonder what
our prize will be.

00:10:53.500 --> 00:10:54.375
Yeah!

00:10:54.417 --> 00:10:55.625
Right this way.

00:10:55.667 --> 00:10:56.875
No need to rush.

00:10:56.917 --> 00:10:58.708
[BOY 1]
Oh, you made it, too!

00:10:58.750 --> 00:10:59.917
[BOY 2]
It was super easy.

00:10:59.958 --> 00:11:01.625
[BOY 3]
This is the best surprise ever!

00:11:01.667 --> 00:11:03.417
-[GIRL] Acchan!
-[BOY 4] Bakemi!

00:11:07.375 --> 00:11:09.833
-Professor Blushenko.
-Hmm?

00:11:09.875 --> 00:11:12.375
-We would like to assist you.
-[BLUSHENKO] Thank you.

00:11:12.417 --> 00:11:14.292
Take care to keep
the others calm.

00:11:14.333 --> 00:11:15.833
Yes, sir.

00:11:15.875 --> 00:11:17.458
Hey. Frowns upside down.

00:11:18.417 --> 00:11:19.292
[ALL]
Devi!

00:11:22.042 --> 00:11:23.625
[BOY]
I wonder what the prize is?

00:11:23.667 --> 00:11:25.375
I hope it's a ticket
to a waterpark.

00:11:25.417 --> 00:11:27.708
I love the water!

00:11:27.750 --> 00:11:29.708
They want us
to keep everyone calm?

00:11:31.125 --> 00:11:32.708
Something is up, then.

00:11:34.000 --> 00:11:35.083
What could it be, though?

00:11:36.208 --> 00:11:38.375
I wonder if Iruma
got through safely.

00:11:39.333 --> 00:11:41.458
[croaking]

00:11:44.500 --> 00:11:45.583
[MOMONOKI]
Reporting.

00:11:45.625 --> 00:11:47.167
The entire school
is surrounded

00:11:47.208 --> 00:11:48.500
by a huge barrier.

00:11:48.542 --> 00:11:50.375
No in or out.

00:11:50.417 --> 00:11:52.958
Understood.
Thanks for updating.

00:11:53.000 --> 00:11:54.292
[MOMONOKI]
Y-yes, sir.

00:11:55.625 --> 00:11:57.958
[DALI] Professor Kalego.
Can you hear me?

00:11:58.000 --> 00:11:58.958
Yes, go ahead.

00:12:00.917 --> 00:12:02.167
It's no use.

00:12:02.208 --> 00:12:04.750
We can't contact anyone
outside of Babyls.

00:12:04.792 --> 00:12:06.708
The only way
we can use devi-comms

00:12:06.750 --> 00:12:09.250
is inside
of the barrier itself.

00:12:09.292 --> 00:12:10.542
But we'll keep trying, though.

00:12:15.125 --> 00:12:16.875
Honestly, this is fun!

00:12:16.917 --> 00:12:19.167
Yeah, I wonder what
they're planning to do next.

00:12:19.208 --> 00:12:20.708
I'm getting so excited!

00:12:20.750 --> 00:12:25.833
Surprises are important,
in life and in love.

00:12:28.458 --> 00:12:30.083
After a quick count,
we estimate

00:12:30.125 --> 00:12:32.083
about 80 percent
of the students are here.

00:12:32.125 --> 00:12:34.542
Yes, and rather promptly, too.

00:12:34.583 --> 00:12:35.708
[KALEGO]
Eighty percent?

00:12:35.750 --> 00:12:37.833
Highly suspect.

00:12:37.875 --> 00:12:41.542
It's as though they wanted
everyone in the plaza, quickly.

00:12:49.792 --> 00:12:50.917
[chuckles]

00:13:02.500 --> 00:13:03.708
It's lookin' good!

00:13:03.750 --> 00:13:04.958
[beeping]

00:13:05.000 --> 00:13:06.125
Uh-oh.

00:13:06.167 --> 00:13:07.500
Where do you think
you're goin'?

00:13:08.833 --> 00:13:09.917
Aah!

00:13:09.958 --> 00:13:11.292
-Ow!
-Goober!

00:13:11.333 --> 00:13:12.542
How about this way, then?

00:13:12.583 --> 00:13:14.542
Let's get to the goal.

00:13:14.583 --> 00:13:17.167
[KIRIWO] Yup.
Now you've got it.

00:13:17.208 --> 00:13:20.167
Such good boys.
Yeah, there ya go.

00:13:22.875 --> 00:13:25.167
This is basically
a rat's maze.

00:13:26.458 --> 00:13:28.625
If they go the wrong way,
I'll guide them...

00:13:29.583 --> 00:13:32.208
...until they're all
trapped together.

00:13:32.250 --> 00:13:35.958
I'm gonna be blowin'
all of you fools up

00:13:36.000 --> 00:13:37.625
with flowers of light...

00:13:38.875 --> 00:13:41.708
...watchin' from the best seat
in the house.

00:13:41.750 --> 00:13:44.375
I know you'll give it all
you've got... [snaps fingers]

00:13:44.417 --> 00:13:47.292
[machinery whirring]

00:13:47.333 --> 00:13:48.375
...Gabuko.

00:13:49.417 --> 00:13:54.083
Or rather... School Destroyer.

00:13:56.167 --> 00:13:57.292
Up, now.

00:14:02.000 --> 00:14:03.500
Switch, on.

00:14:05.750 --> 00:14:08.333
[electricity crackling]

00:14:08.375 --> 00:14:11.542
You and I are the only ones
here in this room.

00:14:11.583 --> 00:14:13.333
No one else can come in--

00:14:13.375 --> 00:14:15.875
[alarm beeping]

00:14:15.917 --> 00:14:17.042
What in the...

00:14:18.375 --> 00:14:20.833
They're not headin'
to the central plaza.

00:14:20.875 --> 00:14:23.250
No, they're headin' straight
to this room!

00:14:23.292 --> 00:14:26.208
Something's wrong.
They're too fast.

00:14:26.250 --> 00:14:29.000
They're gettin' through
the barrier gaps with ease.

00:14:29.042 --> 00:14:30.375
Who could do all this?

00:14:30.417 --> 00:14:33.875
[panting]

00:14:33.917 --> 00:14:35.417
[IRUMA]
Just hang on, Kiriwo!

00:14:44.750 --> 00:14:47.500
[alarm beeping]

00:14:47.542 --> 00:14:50.292
Oh yeah,
it must be Iruma.

00:14:51.333 --> 00:14:53.750
I bet he's reacting
to my choker again.

00:14:55.000 --> 00:14:58.333
But wait,
I destroyed the stone.

00:14:59.333 --> 00:15:01.625
He shouldn't be able
to track me down.

00:15:01.667 --> 00:15:03.458
So how is he doing this?

00:15:03.500 --> 00:15:06.167
[NARRATOR] To answer that,
we need to rewind a little.

00:15:08.208 --> 00:15:09.750
-Hmmm!
-Hmm?

00:15:09.792 --> 00:15:11.333
Did you find
a wall there, too?

00:15:11.375 --> 00:15:12.500
Not a one!

00:15:12.542 --> 00:15:14.750
Why do you complicate
everything?!

00:15:14.792 --> 00:15:15.792
-[IRUMA] Hey.
-[BOTH] Huh?

00:15:16.833 --> 00:15:18.292
This barrier here...

00:15:19.458 --> 00:15:21.083
...isn't it one of Kiriwo's?

00:15:23.125 --> 00:15:24.125
Hmm.

00:15:25.417 --> 00:15:27.292
Yes, it would indeed appear

00:15:27.333 --> 00:15:29.667
that this magic
is the same as his.

00:15:29.708 --> 00:15:31.250
No fair, Kiriyan!

00:15:31.292 --> 00:15:33.375
I wanna do a huge surprise
for the party, too!

00:15:33.417 --> 00:15:36.542
You twit. It's much more
complicated than that.

00:15:36.583 --> 00:15:38.333
I'm coming to your side
right now.

00:15:42.750 --> 00:15:44.042
[grunts]

00:15:46.500 --> 00:15:49.208
Time for Rolling Attack!

00:15:49.250 --> 00:15:51.875
Ow. Owie.

00:15:51.917 --> 00:15:54.250
Oh no!
Are you okay, Clara?

00:15:54.292 --> 00:15:56.125
To think someone
with his limited magic

00:15:56.167 --> 00:15:57.667
could put up
such a mighty barrier

00:15:57.708 --> 00:15:58.917
all over the school.

00:15:58.958 --> 00:16:00.250
Unbelievable.

00:16:01.208 --> 00:16:03.333
If this was done solely
by Kiriwo,

00:16:03.375 --> 00:16:05.625
who happens to be missing
at the moment,

00:16:05.667 --> 00:16:07.792
it stands to reason
he's been carefully planning

00:16:07.833 --> 00:16:10.083
this particular commotion
for years.

00:16:10.125 --> 00:16:12.458
Say what?
He planned a locomotion?

00:16:12.500 --> 00:16:14.208
Hey, Azz, Clara.

00:16:15.917 --> 00:16:17.458
I can't be sure,
but I think

00:16:17.500 --> 00:16:19.417
there's one place
Kiriwo might've gone.

00:16:19.458 --> 00:16:21.167
[BOTH]
Huh?

00:16:21.208 --> 00:16:22.917
[IRUMA] There's no guarantee
I'll get through the maze

00:16:22.958 --> 00:16:24.417
and find it,

00:16:24.458 --> 00:16:26.000
but I'm worried about Kiriwo...

00:16:27.500 --> 00:16:30.250
...so I need to know how to get
to the third-year tower.

00:16:30.292 --> 00:16:31.958
Can you help me?

00:16:32.000 --> 00:16:34.208
-But of course!
-Yup!

00:16:34.250 --> 00:16:36.375
Valac, conjure a piece
of paper and pen.

00:16:36.417 --> 00:16:38.208
[CLARA]
You got it!

00:16:38.250 --> 00:16:39.458
[chuckles]

00:16:42.417 --> 00:16:43.958
[ASMODEUS]
Now, then.

00:16:44.000 --> 00:16:45.917
Here's a rough sketch
of this area.

00:16:45.958 --> 00:16:47.750
-[IRUMA] Wow!
-[CLARA] Not bad.

00:16:47.792 --> 00:16:49.333
[IRUMA] You drew
all that from memory?

00:16:49.375 --> 00:16:50.458
Yes, indeed!

00:16:50.500 --> 00:16:52.167
It was on
the school prospectus,

00:16:52.208 --> 00:16:53.583
so I memorized it.

00:16:53.625 --> 00:16:55.167
Though I doubt this one
has even taken

00:16:55.208 --> 00:16:57.583
a brief glance
at our esteemed catalog.

00:16:57.625 --> 00:16:58.750
Yeah, you know it!

00:17:00.083 --> 00:17:02.167
[ASMODEUS] If we can figure out
where the barriers are

00:17:02.208 --> 00:17:03.792
on this map ahead of time,

00:17:03.833 --> 00:17:06.458
you should be able to get
to your goal unfettered.

00:17:06.500 --> 00:17:08.000
However...

00:17:08.042 --> 00:17:09.000
What's wrong?

00:17:09.042 --> 00:17:10.750
I sense that our small number

00:17:10.792 --> 00:17:12.833
is going to be a problem
if our aim is to find

00:17:12.875 --> 00:17:14.708
all of the barriers
by our lonesome.

00:17:14.750 --> 00:17:15.708
[IRUMA]
Hmm.

00:17:15.750 --> 00:17:17.167
If only we had the ability

00:17:17.208 --> 00:17:19.833
to control frogs,
like Professor Momonoki does.

00:17:19.875 --> 00:17:21.125
-I've got something.
-[IRUMA/ASMODEUS] Huh?

00:17:21.167 --> 00:17:22.875
My soldiers!

00:17:22.917 --> 00:17:24.333
Wait, what soldiers?

00:17:24.375 --> 00:17:26.333
[CLARA] The ones that were
in the MagiApp room!

00:17:28.333 --> 00:17:30.458
You can actually make
those things appear?

00:17:30.500 --> 00:17:31.750
Well, duh, of course!

00:17:31.792 --> 00:17:33.500
I can pull out anything
I've seen before.

00:17:35.833 --> 00:17:39.042
There. There, there, and there.
There, there, there...

00:17:39.083 --> 00:17:40.958
-We can always count on you!
-Not bad.

00:17:42.042 --> 00:17:43.792
[NARRATOR]
Magic paper soldiers.

00:17:43.833 --> 00:17:46.375
These charmed apparati
are obedient workers.

00:17:46.417 --> 00:17:48.750
The more magic you give 'em,
the harder they work.

00:17:53.500 --> 00:17:55.958
-[IRUMA] Awesome, Azz!
-[chuckles]

00:17:56.000 --> 00:17:57.000
Now, go.

00:18:00.292 --> 00:18:03.000
I'll follow the magic of the
paper soldiers I'm controlling

00:18:03.042 --> 00:18:05.458
to find the locations
of the barriers.

00:18:05.500 --> 00:18:07.333
Then I'll promptly report
those locations,

00:18:07.375 --> 00:18:09.208
-wherever you may be.
-[IRUMA] Got it.

00:18:09.250 --> 00:18:10.583
-Be careful now! Bye!
-Take care, Master.

00:18:10.625 --> 00:18:12.042
Right. I will, thanks!

00:18:12.083 --> 00:18:13.917
Oh, but can I run
in the hall?

00:18:13.958 --> 00:18:16.917
Uh! Oh, I don't think
that's an issue right now.

00:18:16.958 --> 00:18:18.042
Okay, great!

00:18:18.083 --> 00:18:19.042
-Off I go.
-Have fun!

00:18:19.083 --> 00:18:20.708
Make good choices!

00:18:20.750 --> 00:18:23.042
[ASMODEUS] The path in front
of the science room,

00:18:23.083 --> 00:18:25.583
in front of
the first-years' cafeteria,

00:18:25.625 --> 00:18:27.833
the hallway in front
of the student council room.

00:18:27.875 --> 00:18:29.000
Mm-hmm.

00:18:29.042 --> 00:18:30.583
You can take
the north stairs.

00:18:30.625 --> 00:18:33.000
Follow the left wall
as much as possible.

00:18:34.417 --> 00:18:36.500
And on the next set of stairs,
the right wall.

00:18:36.542 --> 00:18:37.458
Okay, I got it!

00:18:42.833 --> 00:18:44.708
[ASMODEUS] Next, go right
and then straight!

00:18:45.708 --> 00:18:47.042
There's a gap
on the right side.

00:18:47.083 --> 00:18:49.125
Stay close to the right
and then turn left.

00:18:49.167 --> 00:18:51.292
Next, turn right
and go straight.

00:18:51.333 --> 00:18:52.667
Straight, but stay
to the right.

00:18:53.708 --> 00:18:55.875
You're almost to
the third-years' tower, sir.

00:18:55.917 --> 00:18:57.583
You've got this,
Iruma-kins!

00:18:57.625 --> 00:18:59.833
Turn right
at the next corner.

00:18:59.875 --> 00:19:01.208
Thanks, I owe you one!

00:19:04.292 --> 00:19:06.542
I'm gonna find Kiriwo,
whatever it takes.

00:19:09.958 --> 00:19:12.417
We're going to find Kiriwo Amy.

00:19:12.458 --> 00:19:15.333
He's a third-year
whose barrier ability makes him

00:19:15.375 --> 00:19:17.625
our most probable candidate.

00:19:17.667 --> 00:19:19.417
Capture him on sight.

00:19:19.458 --> 00:19:21.958
Dali, were you able to get
a hold of anyone

00:19:22.000 --> 00:19:23.167
outside the school?

00:19:23.208 --> 00:19:24.792
Zero luck with that, sir.

00:19:24.833 --> 00:19:25.750
[KALEGO]
Unfortunate.

00:19:26.792 --> 00:19:28.708
-Newbie.
-Huh?

00:19:28.750 --> 00:19:30.000
You'll assist me again.

00:19:30.042 --> 00:19:31.833
Mmm, got it!

00:19:34.125 --> 00:19:36.667
Let's start our investigation
of Kiriwo Amy.

00:19:36.708 --> 00:19:38.500
-Yis.
-But, sir,

00:19:38.542 --> 00:19:39.875
what about
the students' safety?

00:19:39.917 --> 00:19:41.000
[BLUSHENKO]
You needn't fear.

00:19:41.042 --> 00:19:43.167
-[STUDENTS cheering]
-[ALL] Hmm?

00:19:43.208 --> 00:19:45.667
Hup! Hup! Hup!
Hup! Hup! Hup!

00:19:45.708 --> 00:19:46.708
[growls]

00:19:46.750 --> 00:19:48.708
Devi!

00:19:48.750 --> 00:19:50.292
[BOY 1]
The Magic Beast Battler

00:19:50.333 --> 00:19:52.708
is having
a dangerous stunt show!

00:19:52.750 --> 00:19:55.208
-[BOY 2] Yeah!
-[BOY 3] Show us more!

00:19:55.250 --> 00:19:58.583
Damn. These people make
so much commotion...

00:19:59.625 --> 00:20:00.708
...and opportunity.

00:20:00.750 --> 00:20:03.208
[ALL cheering]

00:20:03.250 --> 00:20:06.583
Aah! Hey, let's try
to get closer.

00:20:06.625 --> 00:20:08.208
-[screams]
-Hey, I'm standing, here!

00:20:08.250 --> 00:20:10.917
[ALL screaming]

00:20:10.958 --> 00:20:12.667
-[grunts]
-[ALL scream]

00:20:14.500 --> 00:20:15.708
[ALL screaming]

00:20:15.750 --> 00:20:17.750
-[GAAKO] Eiko!
-[screaming]

00:20:20.458 --> 00:20:21.708
[EIKO gasps]

00:20:32.500 --> 00:20:34.500
[ALL]
Ohh!

00:20:36.958 --> 00:20:37.958
Are you alright?

00:20:38.000 --> 00:20:40.000
President Ameri!

00:20:41.250 --> 00:20:42.708
You're unharmed?

00:20:42.750 --> 00:20:45.708
Uh, yeah.
Thank you very much.

00:20:45.750 --> 00:20:48.000
-Be more careful next time.
-Yes.

00:20:50.500 --> 00:20:51.708
[AMERI]
Clean up the rest.

00:20:51.750 --> 00:20:52.875
[SUNNY/JOHNNY/QUICHE/SMOKE]
Boss!

00:20:54.750 --> 00:20:56.875
Listen, all of you!

00:20:56.917 --> 00:20:59.875
Demons should never take
the easy way out!

00:20:59.917 --> 00:21:03.833
If you're going to fuss,
just do it more quietly!

00:21:03.875 --> 00:21:05.542
-[BOY] Right on, Ameri!
-[GIRL] Yes, President!

00:21:05.583 --> 00:21:06.583
[BOY]
You're the best!

00:21:08.125 --> 00:21:09.667
How do you fuss quietly?

00:21:09.708 --> 00:21:12.583
No idea, but the president rocks
so who cares!

00:21:12.625 --> 00:21:14.083
That's brilliant.

00:21:14.125 --> 00:21:16.125
-Get going!
-Yis!

00:21:16.167 --> 00:21:18.083
[AMERI]
What's really going on?

00:21:18.125 --> 00:21:21.083
Is this something that only
the teachers can figure out?

00:21:21.125 --> 00:21:24.667
Almost all of the students
are assembled in the plaza.

00:21:24.708 --> 00:21:26.125
Only a few are missing.

00:21:28.792 --> 00:21:30.125
He's not here, either.

00:21:31.083 --> 00:21:33.958
I'm worried.
What are you doing, Iruma?

00:21:34.000 --> 00:21:35.167
Where are you?

00:21:36.625 --> 00:21:38.167
[panting]

00:21:38.208 --> 00:21:40.500
-[ASMODEUS] Are you still there?
-[CLARA] Hello?!

00:21:40.542 --> 00:21:41.667
-Uh, yeah.
-[CLARA] Yee.

00:21:42.625 --> 00:21:44.208
Good luck to you.

00:21:44.250 --> 00:21:47.208
Boom! Say hi
to Kiriyan for me!

00:21:47.250 --> 00:21:49.542
Okay! Thanks again!

00:21:55.833 --> 00:21:59.250
He should be here,
right behind this wall.

00:21:59.292 --> 00:22:02.292
[electricity crackling]

00:22:05.875 --> 00:22:06.958
Iruma.

00:23:39.208 --> 00:23:41.708
Ki... Su... Ma!

00:23:43.292 --> 00:23:45.333
It's me, Eiko.

00:23:45.375 --> 00:23:47.667
-You okay, Eiko?
-[EIKO] I'm not sure,

00:23:47.708 --> 00:23:50.125
but something amazing
just happened.

00:23:50.167 --> 00:23:53.125
The student council president
saved my life!

00:23:53.167 --> 00:23:55.583
Why is my heart
pounding like this?

00:23:55.625 --> 00:23:58.417
I-I want to talk
to her more.

00:23:58.458 --> 00:24:01.167
Yet, I already have someone
I admire named Iruma!

00:24:01.208 --> 00:24:02.875
What do I do?
This is crazy!

00:24:02.917 --> 00:24:05.458
I've never been in a situation
like this before!

00:24:07.208 --> 00:24:08.958
I think I love them both!

00:24:09.917 --> 00:24:11.875
[NARRATOR] And so,
Eiko delved deeper

00:24:11.917 --> 00:24:12.958
into her yearnings.

00:24:15.333 --> 00:24:16.583
[AMERI]
This surprise event

00:24:16.625 --> 00:24:19.083
even the student council
didn't know about.

00:24:19.125 --> 00:24:20.958
Judging by how
the faculty's behaving,

00:24:21.000 --> 00:24:22.625
there's definitely
something wrong here.

00:24:23.583 --> 00:24:24.792
Where are you, Iruma?

00:24:24.833 --> 00:24:26.375
Doing something adventurous

00:24:26.417 --> 00:24:28.667
and unbelievable,
no doubt.

00:24:28.708 --> 00:24:31.417
Next time, "What I Want
More Than Anything."

00:24:31.458 --> 00:24:34.250
Iruma, please don't do
anything reckless.

00:24:34.292 --> 00:24:35.792
And don't you dare forget,

00:24:35.833 --> 00:24:38.375
you promised to watch
some romantic fireworks with me!

00:24:38.417 --> 00:24:40.500
